A.1 Option 1 – Manual Provider Distribution (Not Recommended)

Description:
This option relies on manually exporting Terraform provider binaries and uploading them directly into Terraform Enterprise environments. It typically involves human-driven steps and lacks centralized governance, making it unsuitable for regulated or large-scale environments.

(Existing bullet points remain unchanged)

A.2 Option 2 – Direct TFE-to-TFE Provider Sharing (Limited Use)

Description:
This option attempts to share providers directly between Terraform Enterprise instances (e.g., On-Prem to AWS). While it reduces duplication, it introduces tight coupling between TFE environments and does not provide sufficient security or compliance controls.

(Existing bullet points remain unchanged)

A.3 Option 3 – Artifactory-Centric Provider Publishing (Preferred)

Description:
This option introduces Artifactory as a centralized, governed repository for Terraform provider binaries. All providers are built, scanned, approved, and stored in Artifactory before being consumed by Terraform Enterprise. This model decouples provider storage from execution environments and enables strong security, compliance, and audit controls.

(Existing bullet points remain unchanged)

A.4 End-to-End Provider Publishing Flow via Artifactory

Description:
This section describes the full lifecycle of a Terraform provider from request through build, security approval, storage in Artifactory, and eventual consumption by Terraform Enterprise. It demonstrates how providers move through controlled stages without manual intervention.

(Existing step-by-step flow remains unchanged)

Advantages of This Approach

Compared to manual or direct TFE-sharing approaches, this model:

Eliminates ad-hoc provider uploads and human error

Centralizes security scanning and approval workflows

Provides a single, authoritative source of provider binaries

Decouples provider lifecycle from Terraform runtime environments

Scales cleanly across lab, platform, and future environments

Meets enterprise audit and compliance expectations

