A.10 Provider Intake Control Model (GIS & Security)

Description:
This section defines the controlled intake process for introducing providers into Artifactory, including who is allowed to publish, how approvals are enforced, and how GIS maintains governance over provider content.

(Existing intake steps remain unchanged)

Advantages of This Intake Model

Compared to unmanaged or developer-driven uploads, this model:

Enforces separation of duties between developers, platform, and security

Prevents unapproved binaries from entering execution environments

Provides full traceability from request → approval → usage

Aligns with GIS security and compliance standards

Reduces risk of supply-chain compromise

Establishes a repeatable and auditable provider onboarding process

